modules.description: Processes ATD (Atype) definitions to generate C conversion functions. Handles record, variant, and primitive types, producing serialization and deserialization routines. Used to integrate OCaml data structures with C code in embedded systems.

Transforms OCaml module items into formatted output, handling errors for unimplemented constructs. Works with OCaml abstract syntax tree (AST) module items and SmartPrint.t structures. Used to generate readable representations of module definitions during code conversion processes.
